(NULL, "Frobnicate, v.:	To manipulate or adjust, to tweak.  Derived from FROBNITZ. Usuallyabbreviated to FROB.  Thus one has the saying \"to frob a frob.\" See TWEAKand TWIDDLE.  Usage: FROB, TWIDDLE, and TWEAK sometimes connote points alonga continuum.  FROB connotes aimless manipulation; TWIDDLE connotes grossmanipulation, often a coarse search for a proper setting; TWEAK connotesfine-tuning.  If someone is turning a knob on an oscilloscope, then if he'scarefully adjusting it he is probably tweaking it; if he is just turning itbut looking at the screen he is probably twiddling it; but if he's justdoing it because turning a knob is fun, he's frobbing it.", NULL),
